did.abstract: Collection includes blueprints of buildings (including Lisner Hall, Lisner Auditorium, Stockton Hall, Mitchell Hall, Bradley Hall, Dorothy Betts Theater, Gelman Library), campus plans, parking lots owned, and expansion programs. There are also images of projects from the Mount Vernon Campus.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Facilities Department of The George Washington University operates and maintains University facilities and provides quality support services to improve the physical environment and the overall mission of the University in the education, research and health care delivery processes. The primary functions of Facilities Management are Life Safety, Emergency Response, Maintenance, Repairs and General Services. They are also responsible for most minor and some major construction, alterations, renovations and support for many University functions such as Graduations, Colonial Inauguration and Registration, etc. They also provide support to Architecture, Engineering & Construction (AEC) during design and or construction. This includes but is not limited to shut off of utility systems, signage, key and lock installation, and landscaping support.
Facilites was previously known as the Physical Plant.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials for this collection include blueprints of buildings (including Lisner Hall, Lisner Auditorium, Stockton Hall, Mitchell Hall, Bradley Hall, Dorothy Betts Theater, Gelman Library), campus plans, Arlie House scrapbook of photographs, parking lots owned, expansion programs, infrared energy loss survey reports. There are also photographs of projects on the Mount Vernon Campus. The material ranges in dates from 1904 to 2008. Note: Not all series are processed. Ask staff for assistance.
The Foggy Bottom Campus Plan, 2006-2025 is cataloged and available in the SCRC stacks.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into 11 series: Blueprints; Blueprints and plans; Brochure and plans; Mechanical drawings; Machine shop plans; Blueprints of six buildings; Airlie House scrapbook and campus plans; Infrared energy loss survey report; Blueprints and plans for campus; Departmental files, and Mount Vernon Campus construction photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes drawings, correspondence, memorandums, statements, and programs. They range in date from 1904 to 2008. The materials concern cleanliness of buildings, room arrangement for events, testing fire alarms, classroom lighting, Recycling Department, conserving energy, policy and procedures, the Physical Plant Department, the Potomac Rose Society, Ecology Action, the University gates, proposed buildings, and the energy crisis.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The images in this series are of different construction projects on the Mount Vernon campus and date from circa 2000-2003. There are images of what the campus looked like prior to construction, during construction, and some following completion of projects. Some of these projects include interior renovations as well as construction of new facilities and renovations of existing facilities. The list of buildings included in these images include: MVC Pub, Pelham, Somers Residence Hall, Hensley Residence Hall, Clark Residence Hall, Cole Residence Hall, Acheson Science Center, Webb Hall, Florence Hollis Hand Chapel, Dorothy Williamson Clock Tower, Lloyd Gymnasium, GW Police Gatehouse, Merriweather Residence Hall, Softball Field, the swimming Pool, the Soccer and Athletic Field complex.
